South African Rail Fleet Needs $15.3 Billion Investment, Business Day Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-09-01T05:21:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/south-african-rail-fleet-needs-15-3-billion-investment-business-day-says.html
South Africa ’s government will need
to spend as much as 107 billion rand ($15.3 billion) over the
next 20 years to revitalize the country’s aging commmuter rail
fleet, Business Day reported.  The Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa can’t afford to
buy the new coaches and locomotives on its own, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing Chief Executive
Officer Lucky  Montana .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  